    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><strong>Söldís Glóðfari</strong> is the master of the Glóðfari caravan â€” a well-worn group of six wagons that have been making circuits through the failing settlements of Svellheim for many seasons. Her coat is patchwork repairs, each patch from a different place. Around her neck, on a cord close to her chest, hangs a sealed clay pot. Something glows inside â€” not quite flame, but the suggestion of something that has been burning for a very, very long time.</p><p>She reads people the way other people read maps. She notices things before she remarks on them. She is generous with what she can give, and precise about what she cannot.</p><p>She will be present during the Siege of Hrafnborg. Her caravan and its people will be there. The party is already deciding, without knowing it, whether those people survive.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
